other_tests.findings: The biopsy sample suggested that the tissue was of nerve origin and confirmed the absence of infection or malignancy. The histological analysis revealed a moderately cellular spindle-cell proliferation set in a fine fibrillary collagen background, compatible with a diagnosis of neurofibroma.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The symptoms and neurovascular findings were unchanged following surgery. At five years after the initial presentation, no substantial change was noted.

other_tests.findings: The results of electrophysiologic studies of the axillary nerve were entirely normal.
